the central bank began signing contractsby which it will provide dollars at a preferential rate for thepayment of 7.8 billion dlrs of foreign debt, under a new planannounced last december.    A statement from the bank said twelve companies havealready been called to sign the agreements and the process isexpected to continue in the coming weeks.    Under the new eight-year repayment plan, private sectordebtors may obtain dollars at the preferential 7.50 bolivarrate by paying a premium of of 3 bolivars on principal and upto 1.50 bolivars on interest. Reuter&#3;